After 10 years of semi-regularly asking @beagleoneism for this clip, it became a running joke, and i really never expected to see it. Then…last night, when the new Beagle Tapes dropped, it finally saw the light of day…or..night. Whatever. This time period was crazy for me. I didnt know anything about the skate industry and i just wanted so bad to “make it.” If i could sit down with the kid in this video and talk to him, i would tell him to have patience. I would tell him to seek advise from his elders, and listen to them. I would tell him that this time in your life is golden and to fully lean into every opportunity and experience. Go out at night. I would tell him to find himself before worrying about a girl. All in all I have no regrets, and am proud of my accomplishments, but i do believe i would have benefited from more guidance. That being said, i try to offer advice to the younger generations that are trying to “make it” when i think it may help. Regardless of weather or not they listen, they wont be able to say nobody tried to tell em!
It may not be #trickoftheyear but its one im real proud of. 🎥 @smallchangeca

Im posting this now to let you know that the opinions of strangers online literally mean nothing. Dont let anyones words stop you. @neverendingspliff is where my music lives.
